From Steve Wu Subject CRYPTO FINAL CALL CRYPTO ' Conference Announcement Final Call for Papers The Thirteenth Annual CRYPTO Conference sponsored by the International Association for Cryptologic Research IACR in cooperation with the IEEE Computer Society Technical Committee on Security and Privacy the Computer Science Department of the University of California Santa Barbara and Bell Northern Research a subsidiary of Northern Telecom will be held on the campus of the University of California Santa Barbara on August Original research papers and technical expository talks are solicited on all practical and theoretical aspects of It is anticipated that some talks may also be presented by special invitation of the Program INSTRUCTIONS FOR AUTHORS Authors are requested to send copies of a detailed abstract not a full paper by April to the Program Chair at the address given A limit of pages of type not counting the bibliography or the title page is placed on all Submissions must arrive on time or be postmarked no later than April and sent by airmail in order to receive consideration by the Program It is required that submissions start with a succinct statement of the problem addressed the solution proposed and its significance to cryptology appropriate for a non specialist Technical development directed to the specialist should follow as Abstracts that have been submitted to other conferences that have proceedings are NOT eligible for Submissions MUST BE This means that names and affiliations of authors should only appear on the title page of the submission it should be possible to remove this page and send the papers to Program Committee A Latex style file that produces output in this format is available by email from the Program Authors will be informed of acceptance or rejection in a letter mailed on or before June A compilation of all accepted abstracts will be available at the conference in the form of pre Authors of accepted abstracts will be allowed to submit revised versions for the pre A revised abstract should contain only minor changes and corrections to the originally submitted All revised abstracts must be received by the Program Chair by July THE PAGE LIMIT WILL BE STRICTLY ENFORCED for the pre Complete conference proceedings are expected to be published in Springer Verlag's Lecture Notes in Computer Science series at a later date pending The Program Committee consists of Stinson Chair Nebraska Bellare IBM Watson Biham Technion Israel Brickell Sandia National Labs Feigenbaum AT T Bell Labs Impagliazzo UCSD Odlyzko AT T Bell Labs Okamoto NTT Japan Pfitzmann Hildesheim Germany Rueppel Switzerland Vanstone Waterloo Canada Send submissions to the Program Chair Douglas Stinson Crypto ' Computer Science and Engineering Department Ferguson Hall University of Nebraska Lincoln NE USA Telephone Fax Internet For other information contact the General Chair Paul Van Oorschot Crypto ' Bell Northern Research MAIL STOP Carling Nepean Ontario Canada Telephone Fax Internet CRYPTO ' General Information August THE PROGRAM Crypto' is the thirteenth in a series of workshops on cryptology held at Santa Barbara and is sponsored by the International Association for Cryptologic Research in cooperation with the IEEE Computer Society Technical Committee on Security and Privacy the Computer Science Department of the University of California Santa Barbara and Bell Northern Research a subsidiary of Northern Telecom The program for the workshop will cover all aspects of Extended abstracts of the papers presented at the conference will be distributed to all attendees at the conference and formal proceedings will be published at a later In addition to the regular program of papers selected or invited by the program committee there will be a rump session on Tuesday evening for informal Facilities will also be provided for attendees to demonstrate hardware software and other items of cryptographic If you wish to demonstrate such items you are urged to contact the General Chair so that your needs will be attended The social program will include hosted cocktail parties on Sunday and In addition there will be a beach barbecue on Wednesday The price of the barbecue is included in the room and board charge and extra tickets may be ABOUT THE CONFERENCE FACILITIES The workshop will be held on the campus of the University of California Santa The campus is located adjacent to the Santa Barbara airport and the Pacific Accommodations are available in the university dormitories at relatively low cost for conference Children under the age of are not allowed to stay in the dormitories so those bringing small children will need to make separate arrangements in one of several nearby More information on hotels is Parking on campus is available at no cost to the However participants must indicate on the registration form if they desire a parking TRAVEL INFORMATION The campus is located approximately miles from the Santa Barbara airport which is served by several airlines including American America West Delta United and US Free shuttle bus service will be provided between the Santa Barbara airport and the campus on Sunday and Thursday All major rental car agencies are also represented in Santa Barbara and AMTRAK has rail connections to San Francisco from the north and Los Angeles from the Santa Barbara is approximately miles north of Los Angeles airport and miles south of San REGISTRATION Participation is invited by interested parties but attendance at the workshop is limited and pre registration is strongly Late registrations subject to a late registration fee may be accepted if space is available but there are NO To register fill out the attached registration form and return to the address on the form along with payment in full before July Campus accommodations will be available on a first come first serve basis for attendees who register by July The conference fees include participation in the program and all social functions as wel